job_description.description: The Senior Consultant Test Management (m/w/d) is responsible for providing test management services to clients in Vienna, Austria. The Senior Consultant will be responsible for planning, executing, and automating tests, designing test cases, analyzing requirements, ensuring quality assurance, managing risks, tracking defects, and improving processes.
job_description.responsibilites:
• Develop and maintain test plans, test cases, and test scripts

• Execute tests and analyze results
• Automate tests using appropriate tools
• Design and implement test strategies
• Analyze requirements and identify test scenarios
• Monitor and track defects
• Ensure quality assurance of products
• Manage risks associated with testing
• Develop and maintain test metrics
• Identify and implement process improvements
• Provide technical guidance and support to team members
job_description.requirements:
• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field
• At least 5 years of experience in test management
• Proficiency in English and German
• Knowledge of test planning, test execution, test automation, test case design, requirements analysis, quality assurance, risk management, defect tracking, and test metrics
• Ability to work independently and as part of a team
• Excellent problem-solving and communication skills
job_description.benefits:
• Competitive salary of €60,000 per year
• Comprehensive health insurance
• Paid vacation and sick leave
• Professional development opportunities

job_description.benefits:

• Opportunity to work with a talented and experienced team.

• Flexible working hours.

• Professional development opportunities.

job_description.description: The Khamenei is responsible for providing spiritual guidance and leadership to the people of Iran. The Khamenei is the highest ranking religious and political leader in the country and is the head of the Supreme Leader's Office. The Khamenei is responsible for setting the overall direction of the country and for making decisions on matters of state.
job_description.responsibilites:
• Provide spiritual guidance and leadership to the people of Iran.

• Set the overall direction of the country and make decisions on matters of state.

• Represent the country in international forums and meetings.

• Ensure the implementation of Islamic laws and regulations.

• Oversee the activities of the government and its agencies.

• Monitor the performance of the government and its agencies.

• Ensure the security and stability of the country.
job_description.requirements:
• Must be fluent in Persian.

• Must have a deep understanding of Islamic laws and regulations.

• Must have a strong knowledge of Iranian culture and history.

• Must have excellent communication and interpersonal skills.

• Must have strong leadership and organizational skills.

• Must be able to work independently and as part of a team.
job_description.benefits:
• Competitive salary and benefits package.

• Opportunity to serve the people of Iran.

• Opportunity to travel and represent the country in international forums.

• Opportunity to work with a diverse group of people.

• Opportunity to work in a challenging and rewarding environment.
